      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i need to ask u something. i think i'm starting to notice something weird with people's voices. like, when someone is lying to me, i don't just feel it, i actually hear this tiny, sharp shift in their tone. it's almost like a dissonant vibration or something? i tested it on my roommate today and it happened exactly when he said he hadn't touched my stuff. has anyone else ever described hearing something like this?",
